RDBMS(Realational Database Management System)
It is an software and it is used to *manage* the database. 
Manage stands for storing data in database, retriving data from database, updating old data with new data and deleteing unwanted data from database.
To communicate with RDBMS software we are using structured query language.
Edgar F codd introduced RDBMS software in year of 1970.
Edgar F codd rules 
   1. store data in form of table (Row/ column).
   2. Only store single value in each and every cell.
   3. create multiple table in database using RDBMS.
   4. using key attributes we can build relation on between tables.
   5. table and column names should unique.
   6. Data entry should verified using * Datatype   * Constraints
